The veterans are concerned about the African National Congress under President Jacob Zuma&#8217;s leadership. JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC)'s National Working Committee (NWC) is currently meeting with the party's veterans to discuss the current state of the movement. Earlier this week, the veterans met with the NWC in what was described as a robust and at times difficult meeting.#SaveSA Pityana on veterans meeting with NWC on Monday &quot;you can&#39;t fix this country with the Pres who brought it where it is&quot; CMThe ANC stalwarts had requested a meeting with President Jacob Zuma regarding the direction that the ruling party is taking especially under his leadership.The veterans, including Rivonia trialists Ahmed Kathrada, Andrew Mlangeni and Denis Goldberg, are concerned about the ANC under President Zuma s leadership.The ANC says it is meeting again with the party stalwarts to build unity in the ruling party.While labour federation Congress of South African Trade Unions (Cosatu) has thrown its weights behind Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa to succeed Zuma, the party says the debate on succession has not officially been opened.The ANC says it views the issues raised by the veterans very seriously, including the health and strength of the movement.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)#SaveSA this is a list of people supporting this campaign. CM pic.twitter.com/mDqzwIScQO(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)